            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#freilichF" start="1242.413" end="x">It was about half a kilometer. So we dragged ourselves through the night and at two o'clock... We arrived at the velodrom Iviere. I was not exactly in the best of health because I suffer from gall bladder. I was very sick. And the daughter of mine, had very much courage. She dragged the bundles. She got a hold of some straw that was lying around on the sides prepared for the people and she fixed a "lay-down." "Here, mother", she said, "here we will lie down and we shall sleep over the night." It was very hard to find some room. People were lying almost one over the other. Jammed together like herring and there was room for 100,000 people. That night was the night just like in a hell... hell.</span>
